Cockpit is an open source web console that provides an easy interface
to monitor your server (a web console)
You will be able to control you server with this tool

You can install it in Ubuntu, Debian, Linux Mint, RHEL, Centos

E.g. in Linux Mint just run:

sudo apt-get install cockpit

after the installation finishes you will be able to access Cockpit on a web browser :

https://ip-address-of-machine:9090

done!

If your browser (like Firefox) pops up a security risk advertising just click ok and continue to the page

Then log in with your server system log credentials

And done!
You have cockpit 
